2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new neural network architecture for semantic segmentation, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses deep learning techniques to achieve state-of-the-art results in semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a new type of convolutional layer, called factorized dilated depth-wise separable convolutions, which involves neural network architecture design. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image segmentation, which is a multimedia application.
